Package: AARP
Title: Forward Model and Bayesian Inversion for Amino Acid Racemization Paleothermometry
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Nick", "McKay", email = "nick@nau.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3598-4834"))
Description: Simulates amino acid racemization (D/L ratios) in lake sediment
    using an Arrhenius kinetics and power-law forward model with seasonal
    temperature splitting and depth-dependent thermal diffusion attenuation.
    Provides a two-stage Bayesian MCMC framework to (1) calibrate kinetic
    parameters (Ae, Ea, x) from lab heating experiments and known-temperature
    cores, and (2) infer paleotemperature histories from downcore D/L profiles.
    Developed as part of NSF project 2317409 "Testing amino acid paleothermometry
    in radiocarbon-dated lake sediment."
